id: pmc-e1jy
title: Release workflow used UTC date for local 2026-05-24 release
description: The Daily Release workflow computed v2026.05.23-7 because it used date -u while the project operator timezone was already Europe/Vienna 2026-05-24. Release tags should use the configured release timezone so manual dispatch near local midnight does not publish under the previous local date.
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 0
tags[3]: github-actions,release,timezone
created_at: "2026-05-23T22:24:21.413Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-23T22:25:12.417Z"
deadline: "2026-05-24T00:00:00.000Z"
author: codex
estimated_minutes: 45
acceptance_criteria: "- Release workflow computes date tags using Europe/Vienna timezone.\\n- Release documentation states the release timezone.\\n- Changelog records the timezone fix under v2026.05.24.\\n- Corrective release is published as v2026.05.24 and npm latest is 2026.5.24.\\n- Clean npm pm install verifies the corrected published package."
reviewer: steve
risk: high
confidence: high
sprint: 2026-05-release
release: v2026.05.24
reporter: steve
severity: high
environment: GitHub Actions Daily Release workflow_dispatch at local midnight
repro_steps: Trigger release.yml after Europe/Vienna midnight but before UTC midnight; old workflow uses date -u and produces the previous local date.
resolution: Changed the Daily Release workflow to compute date-based release tags with RELEASE_TIMEZONE=Europe/Vienna and documented the release timezone.
expected_result: "At Europe/Vienna 2026-05-24, the workflow creates v2026.05.24 and npm version 2026.5.24."
actual_result: "The workflow now sets RELEASE_TIMEZONE to Europe/Vienna and uses TZ= date +%Y.%m.%d instead of date -u. docs/release.md documents the release timezone. Local verification confirmed TZ=Europe/Vienna date returns 2026.05.24, and npm run release:check passed with 18 tests, zero production vulnerabilities, package dry-run, and changelog check."
component: release-workflow
dependencies[1]{id,kind,created_at,author,source_kind}:
